## Roles and capabilities ‚Äî who is allowed to write

A role holds a set of **capabilities** from the closed five-element set. Write authority is *derived*: a role may write a lane iff it holds the capability the lane's kind requires.

### Current role capabilities

| Role | Capabilities |
|---|---|
<% roles.each do |role| -%>
| `<%= role["name"] %>` | <%= role["capabilities"].map{|c| "`#{c}`"}.join(", ") %> |
<% end -%>

What each capability **means**:

- **`author`** (writes `canon`) ‚Äî authoring canonical truth; the **single trust anchor** (at most one role holds it).
- **`keep`** (writes `workspace`) ‚Äî writing to an agent's own durable lane; bytes never auto-promote.
- **`propose`** (writes `queue`) ‚Äî staging a proposal awaiting promotion.
- **`converge`** (writes `machine`) ‚Äî producing computed outputs via `drain` and the workflow DSL.
- **`ingest`** (writes `raw`) ‚Äî write-once ingestion of external source material.

Note: `accept` and `reject` are **transition verbs**, not capabilities. Both require the `author` capability.

